<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 24 at 2:03AM EDT until July 24 at 2:30AM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 230 AM EDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN GRANVILLE...NORTHWESTERN WAKE...SOUTHEASTERN DURHAM
AND WEST CENTRAL FRANKLIN COUNTIES...
At 203 AM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Durham to near RDU International to 8 miles south
of Creedmoor to near Wake Forest, moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Durham, Creedmoor, Wake Forest, Butner, Falls Lake State Rec
Area, Gorman, Research Triangle, Falls Lake and Falls Lake Boat Ramp.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
